				<div class="comment-text">
					
					<p>My daughter was aware of the Furby app before she was able to purchase her Furby (which she waited very patiently for).  Therefor she was quite excited to dedicate the remainder of her time playing with her Furby and experiencing all that she had witnessed with her friend&#8217;s Furby.  She was quite disappointed when we realized that the Furby app could not be installed on her Kindle Fire.  She loves the Furby &#8212; but you can tell that she knows she is missing out on something.</p>
<p>&#8220;Its not a total loss though,  Furbies work fine without an app or connected device, the app just adds a few extra ‘bells and whistles’ such as feeding graphic images of food to Furby, and a Furbish to English translator.&#8221;  </p>
<p>To basically say, &#8216;well your Furby still works without it&#8217; , is like saying &#8216;well you can wear your swimsuit in the bathtub, it still works without going to the pool&#8217;.</p>
<p>We live in a very technological world.  When toy companies create applications designed to enhance the playtime of a toy, those applications need to be supported on all major technological brands.  </p>
<p>So, I guess what I am saying is &#8212; this family of Kindle customers are showing strong interest for the Furby app. on the Kindle and all major smart tablet brands.</p>
<p>Thank you.</p>

				</div>
			
			</div>
			
		</div>

